340 g Pork Chops, boneless
227 g Broccoli
1 unit(s) Sweet Bell Pepper
1 unit(s) Zucchini
1 unit(s) Egg
¼ cup Panko Breadcrumbs
2 tbsp All-Purpose Flour
28 g Almonds, sliced
1 tbsp Zesty Garlic Blend
1 unit(s) Lemon
0.06 tsp Salt*
0.06 tsp Pepper*
2.5 tbsp Oil*

Roughly chop almonds
Zest, then cut lemon into wedges.
﻿Pat pork dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.

Add egg and 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) warm water to a shallow bowl. Whisk to combine.
Add almonds, lemon zest and panko to another shallow bowl. Season with salt and pepper, then stir to combine.
Sprinkle flour over top of pork, turning to coat all sides.
Working with one piece of pork at a time, add the shallow bowl ,with egg mixture, and turn to coat all sides. Transfer egg coated pork to panko mixture.
Turn and press all sides into panko mixture to coat completely.

Transfer crusted pork to a parchment-lined baking sheet.
Roast pork in the top of the oven until cooked through, 14-16 min.**

Meanwhile, cut broccoli into bite-sized pieces.
Core, then cut pepper into 2-inch pieces.
Cut zucchini into 1/2-inch rounds.

Add broccoli, peppers , zucchini, Zesty Garlic Spice Blend and 1 tbsp ( 2tbsp) oil to an un-lined baking sheet. Season with salt and pepper, then toss to coat.
Roast veggies in the top of the oven until golden brown and tender crisp, 8-12 mins.

Cur pork into large slices.
Divide pork and veggies between plates.
Squeeze a lemon wedge over top if desired.

If you've opted to get pork chops, no need to cut them into 2 pieces. Season and prep in the same way the recipe instructs you to season and prep the pork tenderloin. Decrease the roast time to 14-16 min.**